# provides machine-readable citation metadata (https://citation-file-format.github.io).
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "GreenTensor: analytic electromagnetic scattering on a layered-sphere core"
message: >-
  If you use GreenTensor in academic work, please cite this software and the
  underlying IEEE publications listed under "references".
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Denisov
    given-names: Dmitriy V.
    affiliation: "Ural Federal University, Yekaterinburg, Russia"
    email: dv.denisov@urfu.ru
  - family-names: Noskov
    given-names: Vitaliy Ya.
    affiliation: "Ural Federal University, Yekaterinburg, Russia"
    email: v.y.noskov@urfu.ru
  - family-names: Skumatenko
    given-names: Ilya O.
    affiliation: "Ural Federal University, Yekaterinburg, Russia"
    email: ilya.skumatenko@urfu.ru
version: "0.5.0"
date-released: "2026-06-28"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/Den1sovDm1triy/GreenTensor"
url: "https://greentensor.readthedocs.io"
abstract: >-
  GreenTensor is a Python library for analytic electromagnetic-scattering analysis
  on heterogeneous structures. Its scope is restricted to exact analytic tensor
  Green's function (TGF) solutions: the radially-layered sphere (Mie / TGF), the
  infinite layered/oblique circular cylinder (exact 2D analytics), and their rigorous
  superposition into a cluster of non-overlapping spheres via the Generalized
  Multiparticle Mie (GMM) method (Cruzan–Stein addition theorem). Approximate and
  purely numerical methods are intentionally excluded.
keywords:
  - electromagnetics
  - electromagnetic scattering
  - tensor Green's function
  - Mie theory
  - T-matrix
  - generalized multiparticle Mie
  - Luneburg lens
  - radar cross section
references:
